<hr />
<table class="wiki-content-table">
<tr>
<th colspan="4">Memo 46</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="4">ZLQMK/6XY4R/V4D3R</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Sender</th>
<td>Kaitlyn Cantara</td>
<th>Recipient</th>
<td>Amos Marshall and 9 others</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="4">Hi everyone. My name is Kaitlyn Cantara, but you can call me Kate. I'm the new product manager for these items, personally appointed by Amos Marshall himself.<br />
<br />
There will be a few changes to this project. First off, we will be rebranding this item from &quot;Thalbrum Vehicle Security System&quot; to the more fitting &quot;MC&amp;D Premium Vehicle Security System&quot;. This will allow us to distance ourselves from the death of Daniel Thalbrum, and hopefully see sales recover.<br />
<br />
While you may be sad to see Innsbruck go, I must remind how necessary this move is for the health of our public relations. His lack of public empathy towards Thalbrum's death has caused a preventable PR disaster. To make up for this, we will be donating $500,000 to the Manna Charitable Foundation in Thalbrum's name. This donation must be announced publicly.<br />
<br />
Anyway, I look forward to working side-to-side with you guys. As Marshall likes to say, we have a lot of work to do and a lot of money to make.<br />
<br />
Sincerely, Kate Cantara</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="4">Marshall, Carter and Dark, LLP</th>
</tr>
